            <listPerson>
                <person xml:id="saint-1124" ana="#syriaca-saint">
                    <persName xml:id="name1124-2" xml:lang="en" resp="http://syriaca.org" syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">Aha the
                    Solitary</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name1124-3" xml:lang="en">Ahha the
          Solitary</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name1124-4" xml:lang="fr-x-fiey" source="#bib1124-1">AḤḤA LE SOLITAIRE</persName>
                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/1124</idno>
                    <idno type="FIEY">35</idno>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib1124-1">male</sex>
                    <floruit source="#bib1124-1" when="0573" syriaca-computed-start="0573">573</floruit>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1124-1">Peeters, Martyrologe, 168, 174.
Une copie chaldeenne de 1903 de Ia legende de AJ:!J:!a, d'apres le cod. Vat. xxxvn,
appartient a Ia Bibliotheque du Couvent de Notre Dame des Moissons,
aujourd'hui a Bagdad (Catalogue Voste, 87 n° 3, fol. 73v- 106r). J'en possede
une photo.
BS, I, 131 (A. Moreschini) .
Cf. Fiey, Assyrie chretienne, II, 621- 25.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1124">In hagiography: Aḥa the solitary of Resh
          ʿAyna was a soldier in the Persian army; later he founded a monastery near <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/142">Nisibis</placeName>, traveled on extensive
          pilgrimages, and returned with a piece of the true cross. He converted a village of pagan
          Armenians.</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1124-1">
                        <desc>The saint is venerated on Jan 25 in Rabban Saliba.</desc>
                    </event>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1124-1">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="fr">Saints Syriaques</title>
                        <title level="a" xml:lang="fr">AḤḤA LE SOLITAIRE</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/650"/>
                        <citedRange unit="entry">35</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1124-3">
                        <author>
                            <persName>
                                <surname>Peeters</surname>
                            </persName>
                        </author>
                        <title>Martyrologe</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1396"/>
                        <citedRange>168, 174</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1124-4">
                        <note>A Chaldean copy from 1903 of the legend of Aḥḥa, according to the codex Vat. xxxvn, belongs to the library of the Couvent de Notre Dame des Moissons
               today in Baghdad. See</note>
                        <title>Catalogue Vosté</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1423"/>
                        <citedRange>87 n° 3, fol. 73v-106r</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1124-5">
                        <author>
                            <persName>
                                <forename>A.</forename>
                                <surname>Moreschini</surname>
                            </persName>
                        </author>
                        <title>BS</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1425"/>
                        <citedRange>I,
               131</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
